description.text:
Table records user interactions with the PointX app daily, capturing events such as app opens and deletions, 
providing key insights into user behavior, app version usage, and device characteristics

event_date.text: The date on which the event was logged (YYYYMMDD format in the registered timezone of your app).

event_month.text: The year month on which the event was logged (YYYY-MM format).

event_bundle_sequence_id.text: The sequential ID of the bundle in which these events were uploaded.

event_timestamp.text: The time (in microseconds, UTC) at which the event was logged on the client.

event_name.text: The name of the event activity that occurred from the user's use.

customer_id.text: customer identification same values as pointx id in application

user_pseudo_id.text: The pseudonymous id (e.g., app instance ID) for the user.

user_id.text: The user ID set via the setUserId API.

event_previous_timestamp.text: The time (in microseconds, UTC) at which the event was previously logged on the client.

event_value_in_usd.text: The currency-converted value (in USD) of the event's "value" parameter.

event_server_timestamp_offset.text: Timestamp offset between collection time and upload time in micros.

privacy_info_analytics_storage.text: Whether Analytics storage is enabled for the user.

privacy_info_ads_storage.text: Whether ad targeting is enabled for a user.

privacy_info_uses_transient_token.text: Whether a web user has denied Analytics storage and the developer has enabled measurement without cookies based on transient tokens in server data.

user_properties_ga_session_number.text: Session number identifies the number of sessions that a user has started up to the current session (e.g., a user's third or fifth session on your site).

user_properties_ga_session_number_set_ti.text: Timestamp of sessions that a user has started up to the current session (e.g., a user's third or fifth session on your site).

user_properties_ga_session_id.text: Session ID identifies the session that an event came from. For example, two different session IDs are generated when a user has two separate sessions on your site.

user_properties_ga_session_id_set_timest.text: Timestamp that an event came from. For example, two different session IDs are generated when a user has two separate sessions on your site.

user_properties_first_open_time_set_time.text: Timestamp of user's first open in micros timestamp

user_ltv_revenue.text: The Lifetime Value (revenue) of the user. This field is not populated in intraday tables.

user_ltv_currency.text: The Lifetime Value (currency) of the user. This field is not populated in intraday tables.

device_mobile_os_hardware_model.text: The device model information retrieved directly from the operating system.

device_operating_system.text: The operating system of the device.

device_vendor_id.text: IDFV (present only if IDFA is not collected).

device_is_limited_ad_tracking.text: The device's Limit Ad Tracking setting.

device_time_zone_offset_seconds.text: The offset from GMT in seconds.

device_browser.text: The browser in which the user viewed content.

device_browser_version.text: The version of the browser in which the user viewed content.

device_web_info_browser.text: The browser in which the user viewed content

device_web_info_browser_version.text: The version of the browser in which the user viewed content.

device_web_info_hostname.text: The hostname associated with the logged event.

geo_continent.text: The continent from which events were reported, based on IP address.

geo_country.text: The country from which events were reported, based on IP address.

geo_region.text: The region from which events were reported, based on IP address.

geo_city.text: The city from which events were reported, based on IP address.

geo_sub_continent.text: The subcontinent from which events were reported, based on IP address.

geo_metro.text: The metro from which events were reported, based on IP address.

app_info_id.text: The package name or bundle ID of the app.

app_info_version.text: The app's versionName (Android) or short bundle version.

app_info_install_store.text: The store that installed the app.

app_info_firebase_app_id.text: The Firebase App ID associated with the app

app_info_install_source.text: The source that installed the app.

traffic_source_name.text: Name of the marketing campaign that first acquired the user. This field is not populated in intraday tables.

traffic_source_medium.text: Name of the medium (paid search, organic search, email, etc.) that first acquired the user. This field is not populated in intraday tables.

traffic_source_source.text: Name of the network that first acquired the user. This field is not populated in intraday tables.

stream_id.text: The numeric ID of the stream.

platform.text: The platform on which the app was built.

event_dimensions_hostname.text: Includes the subdomain and domain names of a URL; for example, the Host Name of www.example.com/contact.html is www.example.com.

ecommerce.text: A record of information about ecommerce. (Currenntly collect as string)

items.text: A repeated record of items included in this event. (Currenntly collect as string)

source_date.text: Source date of firebase file name

auto_earn_display.text: In case of event delete account the values of auto_earn flag

card_sub_product.text: Possible Values : SCB Beyond , SCB Toyota platinum

each_point_card.text: Point in each credit cards, This value in array format

from_customer_name.text: Full customer name who transferred point to another customer

from_customer_profile_name.text: Customer profile name in application  who transferred point to another customer

search_list_id_scan_and_pay.text: Search list id scan and pay

sku_id.text: The SKU (Stock Keeping Unit) ID serves as a unique identifier assigned to a specific product variant, enabling efficient inventory management and tracking within a retail or e-commerce system.
